{"post-18206": {"user": null, "user_num": null, "timestamp": "1449628450000", "message": "Karnitium is the name of both an island and a nation.  The island itself is almost circular, measuring almost eighty miles in diameter (slightly larger than Ireland).  It is located in the subtropics, with long, hot summers, and short, mild winters.  Its climate is humid, with rain blowing in from the west at least once a week.  The island\u2019s geography ranges from smaller, rocky mountains in the north, to salt flats in the more arid south.Its varied geography makes it both relatively unknown, and extremely self-reliant.  Only rarely do its people need goods that cannot be produced somewhere on the island.  However, travelers from Karnitium have been growing increasingly uncommon, and rumors of unnatural beasts, and inexplicable events cross the seas with ever increasing frequency.Oddly, for most of the recorded history, there have been no people born on Karnitium who can use magic of any kind.Now, emissaries of Karnitium walk the roads, searching for someone, anyone who can help them. \u00a0Those who would answer the call can find them at Greenfield Harbor.thefantasysandbox.boards.net/thread/662/greenfield-harborOOC:This quest line will be an interactive experience, but more constrained than normal, in that there will be a GM (of sorts).  Some general OOC knowledge to consider before sending/creating a character to participate.This will be a heavily combat based quest.  However, for reasons I can\u2019t currently explain (no spoilers), character death is extremely unlikely.Transit to and from Karnitium is difficult for a number of reasons, and characters will be unable to leave until the quest is complete, for better or worse.We'll need at least five people, or it's not going to end well for anyone.", "link_list": ["", "http://thefantasysandbox.boards.net/thread/662/greenfield-harbor"], "image_list": [], "html": "<br><br/>Karnitium is the name of both an island and a nation.  The island itself is almost circular, measuring almost eighty miles in diameter (slightly larger than Ireland).  It is located in the subtropics, with long, hot summers, and short, mild winters.  Its climate is humid, with rain blowing in from the west at least once a week.  The island\u2019s geography ranges from smaller, rocky mountains in the north, to salt flats in the more arid south.<br/><br/><br/><br/>Its varied geography makes it both relatively unknown, and extremely self-reliant.  Only rarely do its people need goods that cannot be produced somewhere on the island.  However, travelers from Karnitium have been growing increasingly uncommon, and rumors of unnatural beasts, and inexplicable events cross the seas with ever increasing frequency.<br/><br/><br/><br/>Oddly, for most of the recorded history, there have been no people born on Karnitium who can use magic of any kind.<br/><br/><br/><br/>Now, emissaries of Karnitium walk the roads, searching for someone, anyone who can help them.<br/> \u00a0Those who would answer the call can find them at Greenfield Harbor.<br/><br/><a href=\"\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><a href=\"http://thefantasysandbox.boards.net/thread/662/greenfield-harbor\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">thefantasysandbox.boards.net/thread/662/greenfield-harbor</a></a><br/><br/>OOC:<br/><br/><br/><br/>This quest line will be an interactive experience, but more constrained than normal, in that there will be a GM (of sorts).  Some general OOC knowledge to consider before sending/creating a character to participate.<br/><br/><br/><br/>This will be a heavily combat based quest.  However, for reasons I can\u2019t currently explain (no spoilers), character death is extremely unlikely.<br/><br/><br/><br/>Transit to and from Karnitium is difficult for a number of reasons, and characters will be unable to leave until the quest is complete, for better or worse.<br/><br/>We'll need at least five people, or it's not going to end well for anyo